    {
      "content": "Manage a delegated administrator",
      "pos": [
        5726,
        5758
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "When you subscribe to <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[wit_nextref](../Token/wit_nextref_md.md)]</ph>, you are given administrator permissions and can assign administrator permissions to other users in your company.",
      "pos": [
        5762,
        5949
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "However, when you want someone else to administer the service, you can delegate this role to a Microsoft partner.",
      "pos": [
        5950,
        6063
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "When you authorize a partner to take on this role, the partner is referred to as a <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>delegated administrator<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        6064,
        6173
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        6175,
        6267
      ],
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Add a delegated administrator<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>: This process must be initiated by your Microsoft partner."
    },
    {
      "content": "The partner sends you an email message asking you if you want to give them permissions to act as a delegated administrator.",
      "pos": [
        6273,
        6396
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Read the partner's terms in the email message.",
      "pos": [
        6402,
        6448
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "To authorize the agreement, click the link provided in the message, which will take you to an authorization page.",
      "pos": [
        6454,
        6567
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        6569,
        6608
      ],
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>View your delegated administrators<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>:"
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        6614,
        6741
      ],
      "content": "In the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Microsoft Intune account portal<ept id=\"p1\">](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=698854)</ept>, under <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Support<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>, click <bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>Overview<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept>."
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        6747,
        6864
      ],
      "content": "On the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Support overview<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> page, under <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Delegated administrators<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>, click <bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>Manage your delegated administrators<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept>."
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        6866,
        6903
      ],
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Remove a delegated administrator<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>:"
    },
    {
      "content": "When you remove a delegated administrator, you remove the partner’s permissions to access and modify your service.",
      "pos": [
        6905,
        7019
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can remove the delegated partner at any time.",
      "pos": [
        7020,
        7069
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        7075,
        7202
      ],
      "content": "In the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Microsoft Intune account portal<ept id=\"p1\">](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=698854)</ept>, under <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Support<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>, click <bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>Overview<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept>."
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        7208,
        7325
      ],
      "content": "On the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Support overview<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> page, under <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Delegated administrators<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>, click <bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>Manage your delegated administrators<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept>."
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        7331,
        7461
      ],
      "content": "On the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Delegated administrators<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> page, select the partner that you want to remove and click <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Remove delegated administrator<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>."
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        7466,
        7534
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a name=\"BKMK_DecommissionIntune\"&gt;</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph>Decommission your subscription"
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        7535,
        7702
      ],
      "content": "Use the following information to remove data from devices and your infrastructure when you plan to no longer use <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[wit_firstref](../Token/wit_firstref_md.md)]</ph>."
    },
    {
      "content": "Task",
      "pos": [
        7705,
        7709
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Details",
      "pos": [
        7710,
        7717
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Cancel your subscription",
      "pos": [
        7745,
        7769
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "To cancel your subscription, you must <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Contact Assisted Phone Support for Microsoft Intune<ept id=\"p1\">](http://technet.microsoft.com/library/jj839713.aspx)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        7772,
        7916
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "To help protect your privacy, we ask you to provide the following information regarding your account: the work or school account you use to sign in to the cloud service, the first and last name of the primary contact for your organization, the name of your organization as it shows on your account, and the complete street address of your organization.",
      "pos": [
        7928,
        8280
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Before you cancel your subscription:",
      "pos": [
        8292,
        8328
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Remove domains from your cloud service<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>: If you added your own domain names for your organization to use with <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[wit_nextref](../Token/wit_nextref_md.md)]</ph>, you need to <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>Remove a domain<ept id=\"p2\">](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/azure/jj151817.aspx#bkmk_remove)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        8340,
        8603
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Save your data<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>: The data associated with your online service is deleted 90 days after you cancel your subscription.",
      "pos": [
        8615,
        8734
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "After your subscription is canceled, if you change your mind, you can reinstate your subscription within 90 days by contacting Support by phone.",
      "pos": [
        8746,
        8890
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Remove data from devices and computers",
      "pos": [
        8895,
        8933
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "When you plan to no longer use the service to manage a device, you might want to uninstall the applications you manage with <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[wit_nextref](../Token/wit_nextref_md.md)]</ph>, remove the <ph id=\"ph2\">[!INCLUDE[wit_iwportal_1](../Token/wit_iwportal_1_md.md)]</ph> app, and uninstall the <ph id=\"ph3\">[!INCLUDE[wit_nextref](../Token/wit_nextref_md.md)]</ph> client software from computers.",
      "pos": [
        8936,
        9288
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Typically, applications and configurations that are introduced by <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[wit_nextref](../Token/wit_nextref_md.md)]</ph> remain in place after you stop using <ph id=\"ph2\">[!INCLUDE[wit_nextref](../Token/wit_nextref_md.md)]</ph>.",
      "pos": [
        9300,
        9507
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Therefore, plan to use the built-in options to wipe devices to remove sensitive information, and plan to uninstall applications before ending active management.",
      "pos": [
        9508,
        9668
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The process to uninstall applications is app-specific.",
      "pos": [
        9669,
        9723
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Be aware that settings previously enforced or set by remain in place on the device.",
      "pos": [
        9735,
        9818
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "When the settings are no longer enforced, they can be changed by the owner of the device.",
      "pos": [
        9819,
        9908
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For information about retiring devices from <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[wit_nextref](../Token/wit_nextref_md.md)]</ph>, see the following topics:",
      "pos": [
        9920,
        10042
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Mobile devices<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>: See <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>Help protect your data with remote wipe, remote lock, or passcode reset using Microsoft Intune<ept id=\"p2\">](../Topic/Help-protect-your-data-with-remote-wipe,-remote-lock,-or-passcode-reset-using-Microsoft-Intune.md)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        10054,
        10283
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Computers<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>: See the \"To retire a computer\" section in <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>Common Windows PC management tasks with the Microsoft Intune computer client<ept id=\"p2\">](../Topic/Common-Windows-PC-management-tasks-with-the-Microsoft-Intune-computer-client.md)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        10295,
        10521
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Remove infrastructure",
      "pos": [
        10526,
        10547
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[wit_nextref](../Token/wit_nextref_md.md)]</ph>has no common infrastructure or software that you uninstall from your servers.",
      "pos": [
        10550,
        10679
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "However, the following are examples of optional tools you might use with <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[wit_nextref](../Token/wit_nextref_md.md)]</ph> that you can uninstall when no longer used in your environment:",
      "pos": [
        10680,
        10868
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "On-Premises Exchange Connector",
      "pos": [
        10880,
        10910
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Tools for Active Directory synchronization, including Directory Sync tool, Microsoft Active Directory Federation Services 2.0 (AD FS), AD FS 2.0 Proxy, and TThird-party Identity Provider.",
      "pos": [
        10922,
        11109
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Before uninstalling a tool or solution, ensure it is no longer in use.",
      "pos": [
        11121,
        11191
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For example, you might use a solution such as the Active Directory Sync Tool to synchronize your local users with Azure AD.",
      "pos": [
        11192,
        11315
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If you continue to subscribe to other cloud services like Office 365, you might need to retain the tool for use by that service.",
      "pos": [
        11316,
        11444
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Remove data from the cloud",
      "pos": [
        11449,
        11475
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "When you choose to no longer subscribe to <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[wit_nextref](../Token/wit_nextref_md.md)]</ph>, you can use the <ph id=\"ph2\">[!INCLUDE[wit_icp_2](../Token/wit_icp_2_md.md)]</ph> and <ph id=\"ph3\">[!INCLUDE[wit_adminconsole](../Token/wit_adminconsole_md.md)]</ph> to actively remove information and data you store in the cloud.",
      "pos": [
        11478,
        11766
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This data can include your user and device information, software you uploaded to deploy to devices, and custom configurations such as groups and reports.",
      "pos": [
        11767,
        11920
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If you do not remove your data from the cloud before your subscription ends, it enters a 90-day grace period during which you can continue to access and manage your data in <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[wit_nextref](../Token/wit_nextref_md.md)]</ph>.",
      "pos": [
        11932,
        12157
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "However, during this grace period, you cannot manage devices by using the service.",
      "pos": [
        12158,
        12240
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "After the grace period expires, Microsoft deletes all instances of your data automatically, and that information is no longer available.",
      "pos": [
        12252,
        12388
      ]
